OL,6,F"She was nine months pregnant and
OL,7,Fscrubbing floors, and that's not what
OL,8,Fshould have been happening. She wasn't
OL,9,Fgiven any pain relief during labour."
OL,11,FJean Sanderson was sent to a Salvation
OL,12,FArmy institution in Newcastle by her
OL,13,Ffamily after she became pregnant "out
OL,14,Fof wedlock" in 1965.
OL,16,FHopedene Maternity Home operated
OL,17,Fbetween 1950 and 1973 in the Elswick
OL,18,Farea of the city and has been
OL,19,Fdescribed by survivors as a "place of
OL,20,Fcruelty" and "like a prison".
